Comment:
Elecam aux usa pour "observer" les elections... une grosse blague. Au moment ou nous parlons, plus de 80 % de votes sont deja effectues dans le cas de ce qu'ils appellent ici: " early vote", ce qui se fait  par voies electroniques ou par votes postales....le decompte se fait de facon automatique. Quand un bulletin est recu par la poste... un agent charge du depouillement du courier scanne juste la barre code et toutes les informations donnees par l'electeur sont automatiquement reversees dans le systeme...et securisees. Ou est la place de elecam dont certains membres ne parlent meme pas la langue anglaise?
Connaissant les americains comme je les vis tous les jours dans les rues de Washington , les membre de elecam seront "bien" recu officielement avec des sourires et des salutations bien hypocrites et vous entendrez sous cape: " what the hell are these people doing here... man? Who the f*ck are they?
Quelqu'un pourrait repondre: 
They are Cameroonians"
Reaction posdible: 
"They are what...? Cameroonians? Where's that?"

Comment:
Bien des femmes frustrees sur ce plateau. Qui elasse, confondent beaucoup le naturel a l artificiel. Chacun veut defendre le naturel avec le rouge a levre et les cheveux lisses. On ne peut etre Belle et 100% naturelle! D ou l invention du "no make-up make-up". Il n y a point de naturel, mais des faux-semblants. On peut mettre juste un peu d artifices ou beaucoup. Chacun son choix. Il ne faut pas conditioner les autres a suivre nos opinions personnelles. C est egoiste.
Pour ma part, les hommes aiment ces artifices. C est pour ca qu ils vont vers vous au depart. Ce n est pas sorcier, tout le monde est attire par ce qui est beau.
Ainsi, ils deviennent jaloux car ils ont peur que d autres hommes vous guettent dehors. L aggressivite de l homme est le resultat de sa propre insecurite. Ils deviennent alors manipulateurs en sortant la carte de " tu es belle meme sans ca, tu n en a pas besoin". 
Par la suite, la femme se sent en confiance qu elle est assez belle sans aucun artifice. ERREUR FATALE car en effet, la belle-famille, les amis, les collegues et meme la famille de la femme commencent a se moquer d elle. Chacun se demande pourquoi une si belle femme est devenue "negligee" apres son marriage. 
Les gens parlent, le charisme de la femme diminue, et l homme en entend parler. Les gens de moquent de la femme qu il a epousee. Des lors, il commence a negliger sa femme, l insolente, reduis son ego, la pietine et finalement va a la recherche de ces artifices dehors.
Adeline(la femme en combinaison jaune) a TOTALEMENT raison. Un homme qui t aime sait qui il a epouse. Et si celle qu il a epouse aime les artifices, il ne lui imposera point de s en debarasser. Il cherchera uniquement des points d entente sur comment baisser un peu. Il ouvrira le dialogue. C est ce que fait un chef de famille.

Adeline(la femme en combinaison jaune) a TOTALEMENT raison. Un homme qui t aime sait qui il a epouse. Et si celle qu il a epouse aime les artifices, il ne lui imposera point de s en debarasser. Il cherchera uniquement des points d entente sur comment baisser un peu. Il ouvrira le dialogue. C est ce que fait un chef de famille.
Name: Merlin Mpoudeu

Mr. Babila I am having a problem with your news broadcast, you make your news boring to listeners by calling the Republic of Cameroon several times during your newscast. If you mention North or South west 200 during your news you would call Republic of Cameroo  200 times, e g.  A fly died in Buea south west regional  of the republic of Cameroon, a woman stole okoro in Muyuka in the south west region of the republic liv of cameroon, a pig gave birth to a goat in Mbengwi in the north west region of the republic of Cameroon, etc but when you talk about douala, Edea, Yaounde, North, west I don't hear you call or repeat the republic of Cameroon, I want to know if it is part of your work ethics that when ever you mention north west and south west region you must remind us your audience that they are in the republic of Cameroon. 
You are a journalist and a good journalist should have a good mastery of language that will not make his her program boring to the audience
Thank you

ATANGAGI IS A CONFUSED MAN. All the laws he has enacted make no sense because he is afraid of Ngor Ngor, the minister of defence and others in the Barbaric regime of Paul Biya. Let face the facts, before he became a minister, he said that there is no Anglophone problem and after few months, he was made the minister of territorial administration and he proudly came on air to say anyone can get a post in Cameroon when they know what they are saying. However, his ministerial position is a trap because if he failed to adhere to the devilish regime instructions, he knows he will be killed. That's the reason of him enacting laws without thinking of the people that are concerned.

Please, let leave him to continue with his foolishness. Southern Cameroon will be liberated in due course. Thanks.

 Une des raisons parmi d'autres  pour laquelle la generation  pre 2000 a tant de mal a s'en sortir outre le fait quelle soit composee principalement d'amateur, il ya aussi le fait qu'elle soit restee uniquement de nationalite camerounaise et ne soit pas expatriee et ne beneficie donc pas du filet de protection sociale des bi-nationaux. Tataw meme chomeur aurait ete soigne gratuitement en France.
Mabouang Kessack qui est si fier de dire qu'il travaille en France ne pense t-il pas que son pays a besoin de lui, que l'Afrique a besoin de lui ?.
je ne sais pas comment  Mr Biya  peut offrir des logements  appartenant a la SIC qui est une entreprise appartenant a l'Etat du Cameroun. A moins de nous faire croire que le Cameroun est une propriete prive de Mr Biya . Assertion que nous sommes un certain nombre a ne pas partager.

Comment:
My name is Bianca Ngwanya from South Africa. I will love to tell everybody on this blog how my status changed from hiv positive to negative, and i am now a living witness of it. HIV has been on going in my family. I lost both parents to hiv, and i have not been able to get over the pain. As we all know, medically there is no solution to hiv. Few months ago, someone introduced me to a native medical practitioner online called DR.WISE. I showed him all my tests and results. I was already diagnosed with hiv and it was already taking its toll on me. I had spent thousands of rands on other medicines before, but yet i decided to try him out. i was on his dosage for 21 days. Although i didn't believe in it, i was just trying it out of frustration. After the 21 days, i went for new tests. And you won't believe that 5 different laboratory results have confirmed it that i am negative. It was like a dream, i never believe HIV has a cure.Â  I just want to help others in anyway i can, i have included DR.WISE's Whatsapp number and email at the end of this message. I have joined many forums and i have posted this testimonies and a lot of people have contacted DR.WISE through me and they were also negative after using his medicine. BBC news even published it live that DR.WISE can cure even Hepatitis, Coronary artery, Cancer, Â Herpes, HPV, Asthma, Diabetes and many others. Everybody saw it and it is now out in some papers and magazines.Â 

DR.WISE's +2349063191711

DR.WISE,Whatsapp number: +2349063191711

Comment:
The problem of water: The natural water supply in Buea is enough for the Bakweri population.
 The natural water supply in Bafoussam is enough for the Bamilikay people in Bafoussam.
 The natural water supply in Bangantay is enough for the Bamilikay people in Bangantay.
When human beings decide to set up structures, they make an estimate of the number of people who will  use the structure, and make sure that everything in that structure will be enough for that number of people. 
If human beings can have that awareness, you bet, the Lord had it before human beings. 
So, all the resources he put in every people's land is enough, just for the people he put in that land. 
Why do we think there are two different sets of Bamilikay people? 
God has a reason for that. 
The other day I thought, my whole life living in the South West province of Cameroon;
 I lived mostly in the Bakweri land, but I went to high school in Kumba. So, I also became really familiar with the Bafor people. 
And yes, I am also familiar with all the other tribes in Southern Cameroons.
 I never heard any one making plans to relocate to Bangantay, or Bafousam.
 Not a Balong man, not a Bakweri man, not a Bafor man. 
If people from this tribes happen to live in La Republique du Cameroon, it means the government sent them over there. It is extremely rare for a Southern Cameroonian to decide to go and live in Bangantay, or Bafoussam. Now that they are crowding Southern Cameroons, when the land in Southern Cameroons is all taken by them, what are Southern Cameroonians going to do? 
Also, why is it so necessary for people in La Republique, to send their children to crowd the schools in Southern Cameroons? Why is it so important for them to learn the English language? 
They have everything the English man used to become successful.
 All they need to do is stay in their own God given space, concentrate, use their own God given things, stick with their own God given ways, and they too will become successful. 
It is high time the government of Cameroon made development plans that will keep every people in their own God given space. There is plenty of water in Bangantay and Bafoussam for Bamilikay people. 
There is plenty of water in the North West region for the North Westerner. 
Instead of expanding the university in Buea, expand the ones in every people's land, such that it will be able to accommodate its own people, then they can teach themselves, what ever they want to learn.
 This message it for Bakweri people: "Vwewor" water is even healthier than tap water. 
While the government will be making plans to even out the population; in such a way that people are not unnecessarily crowded in one people's land, and overusing their own natural resources while there is plenty untouched in other places, Bakweri people should start planting a lot of Banana trees, behind their homes, and start using "Vwewor" water again. 
The strong healthy Bakweri people who were hardly sick, mostly used "vwewor water".
comment_fr:
The problem of water: The natural water supply in Buea is enough for the Bakweri population.
 The natural water supply in Bafoussam is enough for the Bamilikay people in Bafoussam.
 The natural water supply in Bangantay is enough for the Bamilikay people in Bangantay.
When human beings decide to set up structures, they make an estimate of the number of people who will  use the structure, and make sure that everything in that structure will be enough for that number of people. 
If human beings can have that awareness, you bet, the Lord had it before human beings. 
So, all the resources he put in every people's land is enough, just for the people he put in that land. 
Why do we think there are two different sets of Bamilikay people? 
God has a reason for that. 
The other day I thought, my whole life living in the South West province of Cameroon;
 I lived mostly in the Bakweri land, but I went to high school in Kumba. So, I also became really familiar with the Bafor people. 
And yes, I am also familiar with all the other tribes in Southern Cameroons.
 I never heard any one making plans to relocate to Bangantay, or Bafousam.
 Not a Balong man, not a Bakweri man, not a Bafor man. 
If people from this tribes happen to live in La Republique du Cameroon, it means the government sent them over there. It is extremely rare for a Southern Cameroonian to decide to go and live in Bangantay, or Bafoussam. Now that they are crowding Southern Cameroons, when the land in Southern Cameroons is all taken by them, what are Southern Cameroonians going to do? 
Also, why is it so necessary for people in La Republique, to send their children to crowd the schools in Southern Cameroons? Why is it so important for them to learn the English language? 
They have everything the English man used to become successful.
 All they need to do is stay in their own God given space, concentrate, use their own God given things, stick with their own God given ways, and they too will become successful. 
It is high time the government of Cameroon made development plans that will keep every people in their own God given space. There is plenty of water in Bangantay and Bafoussam for Bamilikay people. 
There is plenty of water in the North West region for the North Westerner. 
Instead of expanding the university in Buea, expand the ones in every people's land, such that it will be able to accommodate its own people, then they can teach themselves, what ever they want to learn.
 This message it for Bakweri people: "Vwewor" water is even healthier than tap water. 
While the government will be making plans to even out the population; in such a way that people are not unnecessarily crowded in one people's land, and overusing their own natural resources while there is plenty untouched in other places, Bakweri people should start planting a lot of Banana trees, behind their homes, and start using "Vwewor" water again. 
The strong healthy Bakweri people who were hardly sick, mostly used "vwewor water".
Name: Serge Ewane

Comment:
Human capital should be educated with their own things: language, culture, natural resources; food items, especially should not be allowed to go extinct, and every single resource in that land. A people need to create their own economy. That can only be done when the people are fully educated with their own God given things, and LOVE them, and never replace them with things from foreign lands. And the people need to master their own history too; detailly; and love it, because that is what creates patriotism. When this war started Southern Cameroonians were learning their history from Germans. Isn't that sad?  Because we don't fully learn our history in school. They teach us just a summary of it. A people need to master their own history. When you know something very well, and  love  it, you want to take care of it fully.
 We read at least 12 English books to learn the English language; 7 in primary school, and 5 in secondary school. Then when we want our children to learn our own languages, we give them one little book. And no, I am not at all complaining that we learn the English language. I am just saying that it is time for the people of that land to pay full attention for the children of that land to master that land, so that they will in future create an economy for that land without depending on outsiders.

Comment:
We keep posting #endanglophonecrisis but according to me we need admit that both parties have failed (The Rebellion and Government) . Both parties have failed to protect the people each claim to fight for . Both have massacred the kids , women , the old and young men . We have seen gruesome executions for meaningless issues. We know where to point fingers like we pointed at the #Ngarbuhmassacre (Ngarbuh Massacre) . Yesterday we saw kids massacred in school. I ask myself for what reason ? For studying ? 
Unfortunately I have seen very few people point the accusing fingers to the Rebellion (Amba Boys). We know they massacred these kids. Instead of posting #kumba we should go further to denounce their atrocities same we denounce Government atrocities. Both have failed us. 

 How do we #solvetheanglophonecrisis with the rebellion unable to provide a leader ? A rebellion with No leader and people popping up on social media with insults and from various factions. People of social media who pushed to the chopping of hands and beheadings . People who have given guns to hoodlums. Anglophones have fed a BEAST which today is devouring them 

 How do we #solvetheanglophonecrisis with an adamant government which has been in place for 38 years ? A government which has brought nothing but misery to its people. Members of government have an average age of 60 . Old men and women who should be on retirement but cling to power. How can someone be president for 38 years ?  A government which has failed with the use of force but refuses to see that it had failed . A government which has massacred kids , imprisoned  kids for joking . A government which swallows its own creatures ( so many memebers of government in jail ) for the same crimes such as embezzlement which it steadily practices . 

  Well we Cameroonians let all this happen and we have failed and we need to accept it . It will take and eternity to solve the anglophone crisis , same as it will take an eternity to create a live able environment for its own citizens. 

  With this I come to the Conclusion that the 

THE BEAUTIFUL ONES ARE NOT YET BORN IN CAMEROON

Comment:
Cameroun pays d'outre mer francaise, des vrais feneants qui ne servent qu a se remplir la pense.
il faut vraiment repenser le cameroun
1- ferme l' ENAM  et rajouter tout le batiments a l' ENS
2- supprimer les conards postes de sous-prefet, prefet et super maire de la villle
3- diminuer l effectif pletorique de notre gouvernement a au moins 20 personnes y compris le president et vice-president.
4- accentuer la vrai decentralisation avec des gouverneurs vraiment elus et non les fanfarons qu on nomme avec decret de 17h.
5 disoudre le Senat, il ne sais a rien pour l instant au cameroun avec des voleurs et mourant qu on a la bas.
6-reformer l' Assemblee Nationale afin qu'elle soit plus forte dans le controle des actions du president et ses ministres.
7- eduquer la population afin qu'elle puisse a son tour controler l'action des maires de localites, des gouverneurs et des membres de l'Assemblee au point ou si ces derniers n'assument pas bien leurs founctions, le peuple les poussent a la demission.
8-reinventer les system educatif plus actue sur "Science, Mathematics, Engineering and Technology (education)".
9- avoir un system judiciare independant et digne de confiance pas les pete-pete qu'on a actuellement.
avec au moins ce petit plan d'action le pays va se relever et etre debout comme un homme pas ce genre de pays qui sombre et dans lequel nous vivons actuellement.
vive le cameroun
vive les camerounais
